    <thetext>Build ID: M20071023-1652

Steps To Reproduce:
1. Start Eclipse
2. Open Internal Web Browser view
3. Type in a URL (e.g. http://www.google.com/) and click the
   &quot;Go to the selected URL&quot; button
4. Type in another URL (e.g. http://www.yahoo.com/) and
   click the &quot;Go to the selected URL&quot; button
5. Open the drop-down list on the location (address) bar.

  ==&gt; The list opens, but it automatically closes and refresh
      the current page (= the page loaded on the step 4) 

More information:
This problem can be easily recreated, but NOT in 100%.  Sometimes,
it works as expected, i.e. the drop-down list stays open and I
could select a URL from the list. 

I asked this on the eclipse.platform.swt newsgroup and was suggested to log a defect.</thetext>
